# Brain (`packages/brain`)

- **Deep dive:** [docs/brain.md](../../docs/brain.md) — architecture, extension boundaries, how to extend models and prompts.
- **Secrets:** `OPENAI_API_KEY` / optional `OPENAI_MODEL` in `packages/brain/.env` or repo root `.env` (gitignored). Never put keys in the extension.
- **Iterate prompts** in `src/fme_brain/prompts.py`; **contract** in `models.py`; **API call** in `predict.py`.
- **CLI:** `fme-brain <file.json>` or `fme-brain -` (stdin) after `pip install -e ".[dev,server]"` in a venv; **`make brain-predict`** / **`make brain-serve`** set `PYTHONPATH=src` (editable `.pth` quirks on Python 3.11+).
- **HTTP:** `src/fme_brain/server.py` — `GET /health`, `POST /v1/predict`; **`make brain-serve`** from repo root. Extension calls localhost only; keys stay in `.env` loaded via **`fme_brain.env.load_brain_dotenv()`**.
- **Restart server after Python edits** (especially **`prompts.py`**): `uvicorn` keeps imported modules in memory—**stop and start `make brain-serve`** before live Messenger testing; extension reload is not enough. See [docs/brain.md](../../docs/brain.md) (*Restarting the HTTP server after edits*).
- **Tests:** `pytest` in `packages/brain` (parsing tests are offline). After substantive changes, run a live fixture smoke test if the maintainer has API access.
- Keep **`predict_seller_reply`** stable as the core entry; the HTTP layer wraps it.
